        <prj:note>We will map a rectangular field of about 110" x 790" covering the northern part of the Orion integral-shaped filament in continuum in band 3 and in C18O line emission. 

Main goal is to detect structures in continuum down to  the column density of about 10 x 10^21 cm-2, corresponding to about 0.2 mJy. 

We want to connect the fragmentation of the filament at small scales to large scales. Therefore, we need to recover also spatial scales up to about 35", and hence, require ACA observations.</prj:note>
